			<description><![CDATA[<p>
Ciris Energy is an exciting and innovative start-up company developing unique biotechnology to generate natural gas. As the Company continues to grow and advance environmentally-sound methods of producing energy, it has opened an immediate opportunity for an experienced plant professional.</p>
<p>
<strong>Summary</strong><br />
Design, set-up, commissioning, operation, trouble shooting and maintenance of bench and pilot scale high pressure reactors and associated equipment in support of Ciris&rsquo; ESBC technology development.</p>
<p>
<strong>Essential Duties and Responsibilities</strong><br />
Include the following.&nbsp; Other duties as assigned.</p>
<ul>
<li>
Performs operation, upgrading and maintenance of ESBC high pressure pretreatment reactor systems including preparation of feedstocks, nutrients and supplements, monitoring of conditions, sampling etc., all in a safe, clean, documentable and reproducible manner.</li>
<li>
Contributes to the design, HAZOP analysis, fabrication and commissioning of new pretreatment reactor systems and takes the lead for improvements over existing systems.</li>
<li>
Operates and maintains all peripheral equipment and methods supporting the reactors including jar mills, pumps, chillers, ovens, weighing scales, flow meters and particle analyzers.</li>
<li>
Will play an active role in compilation and communication of test conditions, detailed observations and data to immediate supervisor.</li>
<li>
Will contribute to the planning, design and operation of larger scale ESBC demo plant as needed.</li>
<li>
Performs all work functions safely following health, safety and environment guidelines set by the company, State and Federal governments,</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Supervisory Responsibilities</strong><br />
This position does not have any supervisory responsibility.</p>
<p>
<strong>Qualifications&nbsp;</strong><br />
To perform this job successfully, an individual must be able to perform each essential duty satisfactorily.&nbsp; The requirements listed below are representative of the knowledge,<br />
skill, and/or ability required.&nbsp; Reasonable accommodations may be made to enable individuals with disabilities to perform the essential functions.</p>
<p style="margin-left: 40px;">
<u>Education &amp; Experience</u></p>
<ul>
<li>
Associate&rsquo;s degree or higher in engineering, chemistry or a related field.</li>
<li>
Minimum ten years&rsquo; experience in operation and maintenance of laboratory and pilot reactors and related equipment in a research and development or manufacturing environment in the chemicals, fuels, biotechnology or catalyst industries.</li>
<li>
Excellent mechanical aptitude and ability to use various tools and machine shop equipment.</li>
<li>
Familiarity with PLC control instrumentation and software.</li>
<li>
General familiarity with laboratory safety guidelines and OSHA requirements.</li>
<li>
Familiarity with Microsoft Office including Excel and Word.</li>
</ul>
<p style="margin-left: 40px;">
<u>Certificates, Licenses, Registrations</u></p>
<ul>
<li>
A Plant Operator certification is desirable.</li>
</ul>
]]></description>
