			<description><![CDATA[<p>
Ciris Energy is an exciting and innovative start-up company developing unique biotechnology to generate natural gas. As the Company continues to grow and advance environmentally-sound methods of producing energy, it has opened an immediate opportunity for an experienced energy professional.</p>
<p>
<strong>Summary</strong><br />
Lead and execute technology development program for the separation of valuable chemicals from Ciris&rsquo;s Coal Biorefinery, using a suitable scalable technique. Integrate separation and recycling data into process simulation and modeling using ASPEN or similar simulation package.</p>
<p>
<strong>Essential Duties and Responsibilities</strong></p>
<p>
Include the following.&nbsp; Other duties as assigned.</p>
<ul>
<li>
Design and perform necessary experimentation in separation of chemicals from pretreated coal via liquid-liquid extraction or other suitable techniques.</li>
<li>
Work closely with the Analytical Team and compile distribution data needed for a pilot scale separation study by an outside contractor, and work closely with them.</li>
<li>
Conduct experimental and modeling studies of recycling of effluent streams and its impact on the pretreated coal and throughout the entire process, using ASPEN or similar program.</li>
<li>
Assist in generating any other process data needed for a demo plant design.</li>
<li>
Develop and maintain positive, effective working relationships with co-workers and supervisors.</li>
<li>
Maintain positive and constructive written and oral communications at all times.</li>
<li>
Work well in a progressive, team-oriented environment.</li>
<li>
Have a positive attitude and be a self-starter.</li>
<li>
Promote a positive, professional image of the Ciris at all times.</li>
<li>
Perform other duties as assigned.</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Supervisory Responsibilities</strong><br />
This position does not have any supervisory responsibility.</p>
<p>
<strong>Qualifications&nbsp;</strong><br />
To perform this job successfully, an individual must be able to perform each essential duty satisfactorily.&nbsp; The requirements listed below are representative of the knowledge,<br />
skill, and/or ability required.&nbsp; Reasonable accommodations may be made to enable individuals with disabilities to perform the essential functions.</p>
<p style="margin-left: 40px;">
<u>Education &amp; Experience</u></p>
<ul>
<li>
Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in chemical engineering or a closely related field.</li>
<li>
Industrial experience with separation techniques including liquid-liquid extraction and distillation.</li>
<li>
Familiarity with ASPEN process simulation and modeling.</li>
<li>
Effective time management skills in handling multiple tasks.</li>
<li>
A self-starter and a team player, demonstrating initiative, integrity, good stress tolerance and adaptability at all times.</li>
<li>
Possess superior listening and interpersonal skills, and great customer-service orientation.</li>
<li>
Able to manage a high level of responsibility with poise and optimism.</li>
<li>
Enjoy collaborating with a variety of personalities and work styles.</li>
<li>
Ability to speak and write English at a level adequate to satisfactorily perform the job.</li>
</ul>
