			<title><![CDATA[Technical Fellow, Analytical Chemistry]]></title>
			<department><![CDATA[R&D]]></department>
			<team><![CDATA[]]></team>
			<url><![CDATA[http://cirisenergy.theresumator.com/apply/znGwqG/Technical-Fellow-Analytical-Chemistry.html]]></url>
			<city><![CDATA[Centennial]]></city>
			<state><![CDATA[CO]]></state>
			<country><![CDATA[United States]]></country>
			<postalcode><![CDATA[80112]]></postalcode>
			<description><![CDATA[<p>
Ciris Energy is a start-up company developing a unique biotechnology for the conversion of fossil sources of carbon, such as low rank coals, to natural gas and valuable chemicals. Ciris has a need for a highly experienced analytical chemist to drive its fundamental understanding of molecular dynamics and its impact on the microbial conversion process.</p>
<p>
The chemist will provide their expertise in the advanced characterization of hydrocarbon and oxygenated-hydrocarbon molecules derived from coal, heavy oils, biomass, naturally occurring polymers, and metabolites and intermediates generated by microbes. The candidate&rsquo;s effort will extend from the recommending and outfitting a new laboratory with appropriate instrumentation, interfacing with experts in industry and academia, interpreting the significance of data, and developing and staff. They will interface their activities with those of engineers and scientists doing bioprocess optimization, reaction kinetics, material and energy balances, process modeling, and process variable and feedstock studies. The chemist will also work closely with microbiologists in the development of specialized microbial communities and develop or implement methods that can aid in community characterization. He or she will also participate in the successful demonstration of the overall process at a larger scale.</p>
<p>
It is expected that the candidate will monitor the activities of technicians and junior staff; analyze, interpret, and draw conclusions from data; present R&amp;D summaries at regular staff and board meetings; author technical reports; and stay abreast of technical developments from academia and industry. The senior to technical fellow level analytical chemist will report to the Vice President.</p>
<p>
<strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Advance characterization of natural polymers, macromolecules, monomers, and small hydrocarbon/oxygenates in aqueous matrices.</li>
<li>
Specify instrumentation, facilitate troubleshooting of those instruments, and ensure data quality.</li>
<li>
Interface with colleagues to ensure proper interpretation of analytical information emanating from pilot plant reactors ultimately ensuring successful 24x7x365 plant operations.</li>
<li>
Familiarity with LIM systems and their effective deployment.</li>
<li>
Interface with key external consultants in private industry and academia to expand Ciris&rsquo; characterization capabilities and to assist in process modeling activities.</li>
<li>
Day to day oversight and mentoring of technicians and junior lab scientists.</li>
<li>
Review and exploit the prior art and develop new intellectual property.</li>
<li>
Establish and coordinate safety and analytical procedures.</li>
<li>
Confer with scientists, technicians, engineers and other personnel to resolve process malfunctions and provide technical information.</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Qualifications:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
MS degree in analytical chemistry, PhD preferred.</li>
<li>
A minimum 15 years of industrial experience with techniques including NMR (solid &amp; liquid), LC, LC/MS,GC, GC/MS, NIR/FTIR, and various bulk property analyses.</li>
<li>
Candidates with experience working in coal, biomass pyrolysis, petrochemicals, heavy oil, or petroleum refining are preferred. Waste water experience is also a plus.</li>
<li>
Solid understanding of instrumental analysis.</li>
<li>
General familiarity with laboratory safety guidelines and OSHA requirements.</li>
<li>
Principles of supervision and training.</li>
</ul>
]]></description>
