			<description><![CDATA[<p>
Ciris Energy, www.cirisenergy.com, is a start-up company developing a unique biotechnology for the conversion of fossil sources of carbon such as low rank coals to natural gas and valuable chemicals.</p>
<p>
Ciris is seeking a qualified candidate for a full time position within the Human Resources department.&nbsp; The Human Resources Associate II provides comprehensive administrative support to the Human Resources Director in all aspects of Human Resources operations including recordkeeping, benefits, recruiting, payroll, training and related general human resources areas.&nbsp; The Human Resources Associate II interacts with all levels of staff in a fast paced environment, many times under pressure, while remaining flexible, proactive, resourceful and efficient, while demonstrating a high level of professionalism and confidentiality.</p>
<p>
The candidate must have strong interpersonal and time management skills, high flexibility (roll up your sleeves and get it done!) and a can do attitude. The candidate must be organized, highly-detailed, able to maintain strict confidentiality in all matters and have a polished, professional appearance.</p>
<p>
<strong>Education &amp; Experience:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Bachelor&#39;s degree in business or human resources from a nationally accredited institution, or equivalent combination of education and experience.</li>
<li>
Minimum of two years&rsquo; experience administering employee benefit plans or other human resources functional areas.&nbsp;</li>
<li>
Strong computer skills and experience in using an HRIS system.&nbsp; Must be highly proficient in MS Office Software and a quick learner.</li>
<li>
Strong analytical and problem solving skills.</li>
<li>
Good punctuation, spelling, grammar and attention to detail.</li>
<li>
Knowledge and understanding of insurance regulations, plan designs and third party record keeping/administration.</li>
<li>
Familiarity with COBRA, ERISA, FMLA and related state and federal regulations.</li>
<li>
Strong communication skills, including superior verbal/written skills and presentation skills.</li>
<li>
Proven ability to handle multiple projects simultaneously and to prioritize projects efficiently and effectively.</li>
<li>
A self-starter and a team player, demonstrating initiative, integrity, good stress tolerance and adaptability at all times.</li>
<li>
Possess superior listening and interpersonal skills, and great customer-service orientation.</li>
<li>
Able to manage a high level of responsibility with poise and optimism.</li>
<li>
Enjoy collaborating with a variety of personalities and work styles.</li>
<li>
Ability to speak and write English at a level adequate to satisfactorily perform the job.</li>
</ul>
